What you need to know:

The ban dealt a blow to the Chinese investor who was targeting China, Russia, and other Far East countries where donkey products are in high demand.Mr Munya advised the owners of the abattoirs to shift to slaughtering cows, sheep and goats.Donkey population in Kenya is under serious threat due to the demand for their hides, which are used to produce ejiao, a gelatin-based Chinese traditional medicine.